Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Name: Mummy breast cover
Description: Trapezoid-shaped mummy breast cover with from top to bottom: a winged solar disc framed by two falcon heads; a wesekh-collar; two udjat eyes, a winged scarab; a mummification scene performed by Anubis in the presence of Isis and Nephthys.
